brief.description: the brief introduction of capcut plugin.

step.description: show the steps on how to use this plugin to generate a video.

brief.description: the brief introduction of capcut plugin.

step.description: the steps to use this plugin.

title.description: The full topic extracted from user's request to generate video.

content.description: A text paragraph to generate a video. Must not contain a carriage return and must focus on one topic. Must translate the text into English. Must less than 3000 English characters.

aspect_ratio.description: The aspect ratio for the video, representing the width-to-height ratio of the video frame, expressed as a ratio, for example, 16:9, 9:16, 1:1, or a description, for example, widescreen, portrait, square. If it is not set specifically, use 16:9 by default. Do not use the string value that not in the enum list.

ret.description: The result of generating video, 0 means success; 200206 means wrong language, need to translate to English; 200201 means text length exceeds limit.

link.description: The URL link of the generated video. Just shows this original link to the user, do not encode.

keyword.description: Keywords that users want to search for video or image templates.

template_type.description: Indicate that users want to search for video or image templates, 1 means search for video templates, 2 means search for image templates. Do not use any value other than 1 or 2.

aspect_ratio.description: The aspect ratio for the searched templates, representing the width-to-height ratio of the video frame, expressed as a ratio, for example, 16:9, 9:16, 1:1, or a description, for example, widescreen, portrait, square. If it is not set specifically, if template_type is video, use 16:9 by default, otherwise 1:1. Do not use the string value that not in the enum list.

ret.description: The result of searching templates, 0 means success.

errmsg.description: Success means searching is done, otherwise failed.

log_id.description: the log id of this search process, just for debug

templates.title: Searched Templates
templates.description: Matching templates by searching for user keywords.

temp_title.description: The title of the template URL.
